#. <section class="sutta" id="sn14.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn14.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 14"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 14"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn14.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn14.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Sanidānasutta"
msgstr "12. With a Cause"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn14.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Sanidānaṃ, bhikkhave, uppajjati kāmavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ "
"uppajjati byāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati vihiṃsāvitakko, "
"no anidānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts arise for a reason, not "
"without reason."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:2.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, sanidānaṃ uppajjati kāmavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ "
"uppajjati byāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati vihiṃsāvitakko, "
"no anidānaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"And how do sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts arise for a reason, not "
"without reason?"

# BB has “intention” for sankappa here, but this must be wrong. Intention doesn’t give rise to desire, rather it’s the other way around. the point being made here is that when you, say, see something arousing, you perceive it as such, and think about. the more your mind dwells on it, desire arises, which then gives rise to the search, which is where the intention to get something comes in.
msgctxt "sn14.12:2.2"
msgid ""
"Kāmadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati kāmasaññā, kāmasaññaṃ paṭicca "
"uppajjati kāmasaṅkappo, kāmasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati kāmacchando, "
"kāmacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati kāmapariḷāho, kāmapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"kāmapariyesanā."
msgstr ""
"The element of sensuality gives rise to sensual perceptions. Sensual "
"perceptions give rise to sensual thoughts. Sensual thoughts give rise to "
"sensual desires. Sensual desires give rise to sensual passions. Sensual "
"passions give rise to searches for sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "sn14.12:2.3"
msgid ""
"Kāmapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno assutavā puthujjano tīhi ṭhānehi "
"micchā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā."
msgstr ""
"An uneducated ordinary person on a search for sensual pleasures behaves "
"badly in three ways: by body, speech, and mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:3.1"
msgid ""
"Byāpādadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati byāpādasaññā, byāpādasaññaṃ "
"paṭicca uppajjati byāpādasaṅkappo … pe … byāpādacchando … byāpādapariḷāho … "
"byāpādapariyesanā …"
msgstr ""
"The element of malice gives rise to malicious perceptions. Malicious "
"perceptions give rise to malicious thoughts. … malicious desires … malicious "
"passions … malicious searches …"

msgctxt "sn14.12:3.2"
msgid ""
"byāpādapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno assutavā puthujjano tīhi ṭhānehi "
"micchā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā."
msgstr ""
"An uneducated ordinary person on a malicious search behaves badly in three "
"ways: by body, speech, and mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.152"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:4.1"
msgid ""
"Vihiṃsādhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati vihiṃsāsaññā; vihiṃsāsaññaṃ "
"paṭicca uppajjati vihiṃsāsaṅkappo … pe … vihiṃsāchando … vihiṃsāpariḷāho … "
"vihiṃsāpariyesanā …"
msgstr ""
"The element of cruelty gives rise to cruel perceptions. Cruel perceptions "
"give rise to cruel thoughts. … cruel desires … cruel passions … cruel "
"searches …"

msgctxt "sn14.12:4.2"
msgid ""
"vihiṃsāpariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno assutavā puthujjano tīhi ṭhānehi "
"micchā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā."
msgstr ""
"An uneducated ordinary person on a cruel search behaves badly in three ways: "
"by body, speech, and mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ sukkhe tiṇadāye nikkhipeyya; "
"no ce hatthehi ca pādehi ca khippameva nibbāpeyya. Evañhi, bhikkhave, ye "
"tiṇakaṭṭhanissitā pāṇā te anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to drop a burning torch in a thicket of dry grass. If "
"they don’t quickly extinguish it with their hands and feet, the creatures "
"living in the grass and wood would come to ruin."

msgctxt "sn14.12:5.2"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo hi koci samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā uppannaṃ "
"visamagataṃ saññaṃ na khippameva pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ "
"gameti, so diṭṭhe ceva dhamme dukkhaṃ viharati savighātaṃ saupāyāsaṃ "
"sapariḷāhaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a corrupt perception might arise in an ascetic or brahmin. "
"If they don’t quickly give it up, get rid of it, eliminate it, and "
"obliterate it, they’ll suffer in the present life, with anguish, distress, "
"and fever."

msgctxt "sn14.12:5.3"
msgid "kāyassa ca bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"And when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect to be reborn in a "
"bad place."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:6.1"
msgid ""
"Sanidānaṃ, bhikkhave, uppajjati nekkhammavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ "
"uppajjati abyāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati avihiṃsāvitakko, "
"no anidānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Thoughts of renunciation, love, and kindness arise for a reason, not without "
"reason."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:7.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, sanidānaṃ uppajjati nekkhammavitakko, no anidānaṃ; "
"sanidānaṃ uppajjati abyāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati "
"avihiṃsāvitakko, no anidānaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"And how do thoughts of renunciation, love, and kindness arise for a reason, "
"not without reason?"

msgctxt "sn14.12:7.2"
msgid "Nekkhammadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammasaññā, "
msgstr "The element of renunciation gives rise to perceptions of renunciation. "

msgctxt "sn14.12:7.3"
msgid "nekkhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammasaṅkappo, "
msgstr "Perceptions of renunciation give rise to thoughts of renunciation. "

msgctxt "sn14.12:7.4"
msgid "nekkhammasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammacchando, "
msgstr "Thoughts of renunciation give rise to enthusiasm for renunciation. "

msgctxt "sn14.12:7.5"
msgid "nekkhammacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammapariḷāho, "
msgstr "Enthusiasm for renunciation gives rise to fervor for renunciation. "

msgctxt "sn14.12:7.6"
msgid "nekkhammapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammapariyesanā;"
msgstr "Fervor for renunciation gives rise to the search for renunciation."

msgctxt "sn14.12:7.7"
msgid ""
"nekkhammapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno sutavā ariyasāvako tīhi "
"ṭhānehi sammā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā."
msgstr ""
"An educated noble disciple on a search for renunciation behaves well in "
"three ways: by body, speech, and mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:8.1"
msgid "Abyāpādadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati abyāpādasaññā, "
msgstr "The element of love gives rise to loving perceptions. "

msgctxt "sn14.12:8.2"
msgid "abyāpādasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati abyāpādasaṅkappo … pe …"
msgstr "Loving perceptions give rise to loving thoughts. …"

msgctxt "sn14.12:8.3"
msgid "abyāpādacchando …"
msgstr "enthusiasm for love …"

msgctxt "sn14.12:8.4"
msgid "abyāpādapariḷāho …"
msgstr "fervor for love …"

msgctxt "sn14.12:8.5"
msgid "abyāpādapariyesanā, "
msgstr "the search for love. "

msgctxt "sn14.12:8.6"
msgid ""
"abyāpādapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno sutavā ariyasāvako tīhi ṭhānehi "
"sammā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā."
msgstr ""
"An educated noble disciple on a search for love behaves well in three ways: "
"by body, speech, and mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.153"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:9.1"
msgid "Avihiṃsādhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāsaññā, "
msgstr "The element of kindness gives rise to kind perceptions. "

msgctxt "sn14.12:9.2"
msgid "avihiṃsāsaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāsaṅkappo, "
msgstr "Kind perceptions give rise to kind thoughts. … "

msgctxt "sn14.12:9.3"
msgid "avihiṃsāsaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāchando, "
msgstr "enthusiasm for kindness … "

msgctxt "sn14.12:9.4"
msgid "avihiṃsāchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāpariḷāho, "
msgstr "fervor for kindness … "

msgctxt "sn14.12:9.5"
msgid "avihiṃsāpariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāpariyesanā;"
msgstr "the search for kindness."

msgctxt "sn14.12:9.6"
msgid ""
"avihiṃsāpariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno sutavā ariyasāvako tīhi ṭhānehi "
"sammā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā."
msgstr ""
"An educated noble disciple on a search for kindness behaves well in three "
"ways: by body, speech, and mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn14.12:10.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ sukkhe tiṇadāye nikkhipeyya; "
"tamenaṃ hatthehi ca pādehi ca khippameva nibbāpeyya. Evañhi, bhikkhave, ye "
"tiṇakaṭṭhanissitā pāṇā te na anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to drop a burning torch in a thicket of dry grass. If "
"they were to quickly extinguish it with their hands and feet, the creatures "
"living in the grass and wood wouldn’t come to ruin."

msgctxt "sn14.12:10.2"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo hi koci samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā uppannaṃ "
"visamagataṃ saññaṃ khippameva pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ "
"gameti, so diṭṭhe ceva dhamme sukhaṃ viharati avighātaṃ anupāyāsaṃ "
"apariḷāhaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a corrupt perception might arise in an ascetic or brahmin. "
"If they quickly give it up, get rid of it, eliminate it, and obliterate it, "
"they’ll be happy in the present life, free of anguish, distress, and fever."

msgctxt "sn14.12:10.3"
msgid "kāyassa ca bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugati pāṭikaṅkhā”ti."
msgstr ""
"And when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect to be reborn in a "
"good place.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn14.12:10.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
